// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// T123 — non-default config: `spaces_inside_braces = true` adds
// one space pad on EACH side of a `ConcatExpr`'s `{` / `}`
// (per `formatting-rules.contract.md` §4 ConcatExpr toggle).
// Default behavior is no inside-padding; this fixture flips the
// knob and verifies the output reflects the change.
//
// `formatNode(ConcatExpr)` reads `cfg_.spaces_inside_braces` and
// switches the open/close braces between `{`/`}` (default) and
// `{ `/` }` (toggle on); the inter-element comma+space stays at
// `, ` either way.
//
// Default canonical: `{a, b, c}`
// Toggle-on canonical: `{ a, b, c }`

// RUN: rm -rf %t.sib && mkdir -p %t.sib
// RUN: printf 'spaces_inside_braces = true\n' > %t.sib/.nsl-fmt.toml
// RUN: printf 'module m { reg q[24] = {a, b, c}; }\n' > %t.sib/m.nsl
// RUN: cd %t.sib && nsl-fmt m.nsl | FileCheck %s
//
// CHECK: { a, b, c }
